1:1 COMMENT "# zerovalues.z -- bare type names construct zero values."
1:57 EOL "\n"
2:1 COMMENT "#"
2:2 EOL "\n"
3:1 COMMENT "# A bare type name in a runtime value position is a zero-argument"
3:66 EOL "\n"
4:1 COMMENT "# `.create` construction: numerics bind zero, String binds the empty"
4:69 EOL "\n"
5:1 COMMENT "# owned string, and records/classes fill their declared defaults (a"
5:68 EOL "\n"
6:1 COMMENT "# body-carrying user create is called instead). The explicit dotted"
6:68 EOL "\n"
7:1 COMMENT "# form (`u64.create`) is the same construction; binding, call-arg,"
7:67 EOL "\n"
8:1 COMMENT "# return, and reassignment positions all accept it. Generic type"
8:65 EOL "\n"
9:1 COMMENT "# arguments are unaffected: `(Map key: String value: u64)` still"
9:65 EOL "\n"
10:1 COMMENT "# reads its labels as types."
10:29 EOL "\n"
